    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA275-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu ciṟaippuṟamākat talaimakaṉatu varavuṇarntu vaṟpuṟuppa vaṉpuṟai yetirmoḻintatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what was said in the face of encouragement when [the confidante] encouraged [HER] after having understood HIS coming when he was behind the fence.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA275">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            cenne larinar kūrvāṭ puṇṇuṟak</l>
<l>            kāṇā mutaloṭu pōnteṉap pūvē</l>
<l>            paṭaiyoṭuṅ katiroṭu mayaṅkiya paṭukkait</l>
<l>            tammuṟu viḻuma maṟiyā maṉamel</l>
<l>            teṟukati riṉṟuyiṟ pacuvāy tiṟakkum </l>
<l>            pētai neytaṟ perunīrc cērppaṟ</l>
<l>            kiyāṉiṉain tiraṅkē ṉāka nōyikaḻn</l>
<l>            taṟaṉi lāḷaṉ pukaḻpeṟa</l>
<l>            peṟiṉum vallēṉmaṟ ṟōḻi yāṉē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Negligent of pain, since I don’t feel pity, thinking of</l>
<l rend="indent">the man from the coast of the big water with foolish blue waterlilies,</l>
<l rend="indent2">that open [their] green mouths from sweet sleep in the scorching rays,</l>
<l rend="indent2">[their] minds soft, without knowing of the distress they have<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">tam uṟu</term>: since we see an oblique here, uṟu cannot be taken as a transitive verb, and it would be more precise to translate "not knowing of the distress that occurred to them".</note></l>
<l rend="indent2">on [their] bed, mixed up with the [cutting] tools and with the ears</l>
<l rend="indent2">– flowers<note place="foot">Syntax is awkward in these first two lines. The only clear mark is -<term xml:lang="ta">ē</term> at the end, and I suggest to take it seriously, all the more since it is not possible to integrate <term xml:lang="ta">pūvē</term> in a natural way into the following clause. Still problematic is the <term xml:lang="ta">pōnteṉa</term>, doubtless absolutive plus <term xml:lang="ta">eṉa</term>, but here obviously not in a causal sense, but rather reminding of the way the ideophones work.</note>, gone with the base, not seeing</l>
<l rend="indent2">that they are wounded by the sharp sickles of the cutters of red paddy -</l>
<l rend="indent">even if I get, to get praise, [that] virtueless man,</l>
<l>I won’t have the strength [anymore], friend.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
